172
00:15:06,550 --> 00:15:08,520
游过了泰晤士河，从出水口跳了出来
He swam up the Thames and out through the plughole,

173
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:13,200
把正做饭的妈妈和惠特克夫人吓了一跳
giving the cook mama and Mrs Whittaker quite a shock.

174
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:17,070
女孩们听到吵闹声
When the girls heard all the commotion

175
00:15:17,570 --> 00:15:19,040
就跑到了厨房，她们给他…
They run to the kitchen where they gave him

176
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:22,630
擦干净，喂吃的，还吻了他
a good scrub, a mackerel and a kiss.

177
00:15:25,020 --> 00:15:28,520
你们知道吻他的时候，他变成什么了？
And as they kissed him guess what he turned into?

178
00:15:29,090 --> 00:15:30,680
一个英俊的王子！
A handsome prince!

179
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:32,480
一个短尾巴的信天翁
A short-tailed Albatross.

180
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:40,990
不过翅膀大到可以把女儿们好好的抱住
With wings big enough that he could wrap them both around his two girls together

181
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:43,810
好了，去睡觉吧
Now girls, time for bed. Come on

182
00:15:44,460 --> 00:15:45,830
把小马牵到马厩里
Take the horses to the stable

183
00:15:46,370 --> 00:15:47,380
一分钟后弄好啊
You have exactly a minute

184
00:15:47,740 --> 00:15:48,570
晚安
Good night

185
00:15:48,880 --> 00:15:50,260
喂草清理后就去睡觉
feed them brush them and to bed.

186
00:15:51,930 --> 00:15:53,140
辛普森太太也在吗？
Will Mrs Simpson be there?

187
00:15:54,090 --> 00:15:55,080
我哥哥坚持让她来
My brother's insisting.

188
00:15:56,910 --> 00:15:57,820
他是认真的？
Is he serious?

189
00:15:58,650 --> 00:16:01,180
是说请我们吃饭？
About our coming to dinner?

190
00:16:01,770 --> 00:16:03,480
不。我是问对她的感情
No. About her!

191
00:16:06,390 --> 00:16:07,800
一个结婚的女人？不太可能
A married woman? He can't be.

192
00:16:08,430 --> 00:16:12,310
她倒有可能。对了，我找到个有意思的人选
She can. By the way I think I found someone rather interesting.

193
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,670
在哈雷大街，一个大夫
On Harley Street. A doctor.

194
00:16:15,020 --> 00:16:18,660
这绝对不行。我不再和你讨论这事儿了
Out of the question. I'm not having this conversation again.

195
00:16:19,170 --> 00:16:20,870
肯定没戏
The matter's settled.

196
00:16:21,580 --> 00:16:23,240
他的治疗方法很特别…
His approach seems rather different....

197
00:16:25,910 --> 00:16:26,670
开始？
Now?

198
00:16:28,370 --> 00:16:28,900
开始！
Now!

199
00:16:37,110 --> 00:16:39,850
“现在我们严冬般的宿怨…”
（莎士比亚戏剧《理查三世》第一场）
“Now is the winter of our discontent

200
00:16:39,910 --> 00:16:43,840
给这颗约克的红日照耀成为夏景
（莎士比亚戏剧《理查三世》第一场）
Made glorious summer by this sun of York.”

201
00:16:44,540 --> 00:16:47,470
那笼罩我们王室的愁云…
（理查此番演说表达了嫉妒篡位的野心）
“And all the clouds that lour'd upon our house

202
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:49,520
都埋进了海洋深处。
（理查此番演说表达了嫉妒篡位的野心）
In the deep bosom of the ocean buried.

203
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:54,690
现在我们额前已经戴上了胜利的花环…
Now are our brows bound with victorious wreaths;

204
00:16:54,990 --> 00:16:56,410
谢谢
Thank you.

205
00:16:58,990 --> 00:17:01,160
试演的不错，您是…
Lovely diction, Mr...

206
00:17:01,730 --> 00:17:02,950
罗格，莱诺·罗格
Logue. Lionel Logue.

207
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:04,650
好吧，罗格先生
Well, Mr Logue,

208
00:17:05,620 --> 00:17:11,130
我没感受到想当皇帝到心里扭曲的灵魂呐喊
I'm not hearing the cries of a deformed creature yearning to be King.

209
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:16,420
也没感受到理查三世的领袖风范
Nor did I realize Richard the Third was King of the Colonies.

210
00:17:19,970 --> 00:17:21,660
台词我都会背
I do know all the lines.

211
00:17:22,050 --> 00:17:23,190
我以前演过的
I've played the role before.

212
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:24,980
- 在悉尼？
- 佩斯市（澳大利亚城市）
- Sydney? - Perth.

213
00:17:25,690 --> 00:17:29,320
- 喜欢戏剧的小镇，是吧？
- 大家都很热情
- Major theater town, is it? - Enthusiastic.

214
00:17:30,190 --> 00:17:32,330
- 哦
- 我很受好评的
- Ah. - I was well reviewed.

215
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:38,650
那…个…莱诺
Yes...well...Lionel,

216
00:17:39,190 --> 00:17:43,500
我想对于我们剧团来说，您的…
I think our dramatic society is looking for

217
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,490
…年龄大了点
someone slightly younger

218
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:50,830
也缺点儿王者风范
and a little more regal.

219
00:18:02,390 --> 00:18:04,700
要把最外面的先关上
You have to shut that one first.

220
00:18:05,260 --> 00:18:07,200
关了第一扇门才行
Close that one first, that

221
00:18:09,690 --> 00:18:11,910
你怎么找到这个…医师的？
Where did you find this...physician?

222
00:18:12,070 --> 00:18:15,270
来源保密，线人在谢德集市的法国造型小店旁边
Classifieds, next to “French model, Shepherd's Market”.

223
00:18:16,430 --> 00:18:17,500
这人强力推荐他
He comes highly recommended.

224
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:20,210
收费不少，用来帮助穷人
Charges substantial fees in order to help the poor.

225
00:18:20,710 --> 00:18:22,260
哎呀，难不成是个共党分子？
Oh dear, perhaps he's a Bolshevik?!

226
00:18:25,950 --> 00:18:28,300
他没接待员，说是凡事从简
He has no receptionist. He likes to keep things simple.

227
00:18:32,940 --> 00:18:33,820
约翰逊一家来了
The Johnsons.

228
00:18:45,540 --> 00:18:48,270
你能进去了，约翰逊先生
You can go in now, “Mr. Johnson”.

229
00:18:49,530 --> 00:18:53,590
莱诺说，您可以在这里等着，夫人
Lionel says...wait here if you wish, Mrs Johnson.

230
00:18:54,360 --> 00:19:00,490
天气这…这么好，也可以…
Or, it being a p-pleasant day,

231
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:07,150
…出…出去散步
p-perhaps take a stroll.

232
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:11,520
这样行么，莱诺？
Was that alright...Lionel?

233
00:19:14,360 --> 00:19:15,380
非常好，威利！
Marvellous, Willy

234
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:17,670
你可以在这儿等你妈妈
You can stay here and wait for your mum.

235
00:19:20,270 --> 00:19:23,980
约翰逊夫人。先生，请进
Mrs Johnson. Mr.Johnson, do come in.

236
00:19:43,930 --> 00:19:45,040
想要吃糖吗？
Would you like a sweetie

237
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:46,720
威利这小伙不错
He's a good lad, Willy.

238
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:49,010
刚开始过来时
He could hardly make a sound, you know,

239
00:19:49,550 --> 00:19:50,580
他都发不出声来
when he first came to me.

240
00:19:59,840 --> 00:20:01,590
我儿子们做的，还不错吧？
My boys made those. Good, aren't they.

241
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:05,480
请随便坐
Please, make yourself comfortable.

242
00:20:22,210 --> 00:20:23,780
我听说不能坐的太近
I was told not not to sit too close.

243
00:20:32,380 --> 00:20:36,430
还有说话的时候，要让王子先选择话题
when speaking with a prince, one waits for the prince to choose the topic.

244
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:48,290
等着我…才…才开始
Waiting for me to… commence a conversation

245
00:20:48,670 --> 00:20:50,680
那可要等上很久
one can wait a rather long wait.

246
00:21:00,060 --> 00:21:01,350
那么就讲些笑话？
Do you know any jokes?

247
00:21:08,410 --> 00:21:10,480
把握节奏…我可不擅长
Timing isn't my strong suit.

248
00:21:13,310 --> 00:21:14,430
来杯茶？
Cuppa tea?

249
00:21:15,620 --> 00:21:16,920
不了，谢谢
No thank you.

250
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:18,890
我来一杯吧
I think I'll have one.

251
00:21:31,870 --> 00:21:33,580
罗格医生，你不该开始治疗了吗？
Aren't you going to start treating me Dr Logue?

252
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:36,460
你真正愿意配合了，我才开始
Only if you're interested in being treated.

253
00:21:37,330 --> 00:21:40,210
叫我莱诺就好
Please, call me Lionel.

254
00:21:40,950 --> 00:21:44,110
我还是称呼你医生吧
I… I prefer Doctor.

255
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:49,110
我喜欢莱诺这名儿。怎么称呼您？
I prefer Lionel. What'll I call you?

256
00:21:49,730 --> 00:21:54,860
尊贵的殿下，然后说公爵
Your Royal Highness, then Sir after that.

257
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:57,790
太正式了点，还是叫名字吧
A bit formal for here. I prefer names

258
00:21:58,640 --> 00:22:04,980
阿尔伯特·福德里克·亚瑟·乔治王子？
Prince Albert Frederick Arthur George?

259
00:22:05,900 --> 00:22:07,120
叫伯蒂好么？
How about Bertie?

260
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:12,030
我家人才能这么说
Only my family uses that.

261
00:22:12,780 --> 00:22:17,180
那正好了，在这儿，我们最好是平等关系
Perfect. In here, it's better if we're equals.

262
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:25,400
和你一样的话，我就不会来了
If we were equal.. I wouldn't be here.

263
00:22:26,530 --> 00:22:33,090
我陪陪家人就行，没人管我结巴的事儿
I'd be.. at home with my wife and no-one would give a damn.

264
00:22:33,910 --> 00:22:35,110
请别这样
Please don't do that.

265
00:22:35,990 --> 00:22:36,910
怎么？
I'm sorry?

266
00:22:37,570 --> 00:22:41,060
这样吸烟就是自己找死
I believe sucking smoke into your lungs will kill you.

267
00:22:41,710 --> 00:22:45,210
我的医生说烟能放松喉部
My physicians say it relaxes the throat.

268
00:22:45,810 --> 00:22:46,730
一群笨蛋
They're idiots.

269
00:22:47,060 --> 00:22:48,160
他们可是受过爵位的医生
They've all been knighted.

270
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:49,940
那就是官方的笨蛋了
Makes it official then.

271
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:54,250
我的城堡，我来做主
My 'castle', my rules.

272
00:22:59,280 --> 00:23:00,180
麻烦了
Thank you

273
00:23:02,290 --> 00:23:03,610
你最早的回忆是什么？
What was your earliest memory?

274
00:23:05,560 --> 00:23:06,680
什么乱七八糟的
What an earth do you mean?

275
00:23:07,150 --> 00:23:08,230
你最先记起的事儿
Your first recollection.

276
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:09,900
我不是来…
I'm not…

277
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:14,300
…来讨论个人隐私的
here to discuss personal matters.

278
00:23:14,790 --> 00:23:15,920
那您干什么来了？
Why're you here then?

279
00:23:16,210 --> 00:23:17,670
因为我非常的结巴！
Because I bloody well stammer!

280
00:23:19,590 --> 00:23:20,620
脾气很烈嘛
You have a bit of a temper.

281
00:23:21,220 --> 00:23:22,510
我的缺点之一
One of my many faults.

282
00:23:24,060 --> 00:23:25,250
什么时候开始结巴的？
When did the defect start?

283
00:23:25,600 --> 00:23:26,910
我从小就这样！
I've always been this way!

284
00:23:27,350 --> 00:23:28,080
我很怀疑
I doubt that.

285
00:23:28,390 --> 00:23:31,500
别…别和我争！是我结巴！
Don't.. tell me! It's my stammer!

286
00:23:31,620 --> 00:23:33,130
我研究这领域，我保证…
It's my field. I assure you,

287
00:23:33,580 --> 00:23:36,060
没有小孩生下来就是结巴的
no infant starts to speak with a stammer.

288
00:23:36,580 --> 00:23:37,530
什么时候开始的？
When did it start?

289
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:41,540
四五岁吧
Four or five.

290
00:23:41,980 --> 00:23:42,990
这很典型
That's typical.

291
00:23:43,710 --> 00:23:45,510
其他人也这么说
So I've been told.

292
00:23:46,750 --> 00:23:48,710
我印象里就没有不结巴的时候
I can't remember not doing it.

293
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:52,800
这我相信。想事儿的时候会结巴吗？
I can believe that. Do you hesitate when you think?

294
00:23:53,370 --> 00:23:54,510
别开玩笑了
Don't be ridiculous.

295
00:23:55,230 --> 00:23:56,510
自言自语的时候呢？
How about when you talk to yourself?

296
00:23:59,310 --> 00:24:01,350
每个人都有嘟囔的时候，伯蒂
Everyone natters occasionally, Bertie.

297
00:24:01,890 --> 00:24:03,020
别这么叫我！
Stop calling me that!

298
00:24:03,670 --> 00:24:04,660
我不会叫你其他名字了
I'm not going to call you anything else.

299
00:24:05,050 --> 00:24:06,130
那咱们谈话结束
Then we shan't speak!

300
00:24:22,350 --> 00:24:24,020
大夫，咨询也要收钱的吧？
Are you charging for this, Doctor?

301
00:24:26,970 --> 00:24:27,960
一大笔呢
A fortune.

302
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:35,980
茶待会喝
I'll just save that brew

303
00:24:37,770 --> 00:24:41,470
那你自言自语的时候，结巴吗？
So, when you talk to yourself, do you stammer?

304
00:24:42,090 --> 00:24:45,320
当然不会！
Of course not!

305
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:49,950
这说明你的缺陷不是不可改变的
That proves your impediment isn't a permanent part of you.

306
00:24:50,370 --> 00:24:51,380
你觉得病因是什么？
What do you think was the cause?

307
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:57,470
我怎么知道！我…我也不关心！
I don't know! I… don't care!

308
00:24:59,060 --> 00:25:03,930
我结巴，没人能治得好
I stammer. And no one can fix it.

309
00:25:04,490 --> 00:25:07,990
我打赌，你在这儿就能流畅的阅读
I'll bet you, you can read flawlessly, right here, right now.

310
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:11,950
如果我赌赢了，我要继续问你些问题
And if I win the bet, I get to ask you more questions.

311
00:25:12,390 --> 00:25:13,250
要是我赢？
And if I win?

312
00:25:13,710 --> 00:25:14,960
你可以不回答么
You don't have to answer them.

313
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:19,520
一般…都是赌钱的
One usually… wagers money.

314
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:23,480
赌注一先令，赌个意思？你的钱呢
A bob each to keep it sweet? Let's see your shilling.

315
00:25:24,120 --> 00:25:27,510
我…我…随身不带钱
I don't… carry money.

316
00:25:28,070 --> 00:25:29,830
我就觉得你会这么说
I had a funny feeling you mightn't.

317
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:33,000
我帮你下注，下回还给我就好
I'll stake you. And you can pay me back next time.

318
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:34,980
如果还有下回的话
If there is a next time.

319
00:25:35,510 --> 00:25:37,270
我也没确定要继续治疗你
I haven't agreed to take you on yet

320
00:25:41,860 --> 00:25:45,810
请站起来，读读这段，从这里
So please stand, and take a look at that, from there

321
00:25:51,080 --> 00:25:53,990
这我读不了
I can't read this.

322
00:25:54,470 --> 00:25:56,100
你试都不试，先输我一先令了
Then you owe me a shilling for not trying.

323
00:26:02,260 --> 00:26:13,660
“生…生…存还是毁灭”
（莎士比亚《哈姆雷特》）
“To.. to..be or not to be,

324
00:26:14,130 --> 00:26:18,970
“这是……”     见鬼
That… is..”  damn

325
00:26:21,480 --> 00:26:22,960
我还没完呢
I haven't finished yet.

326
00:26:33,280 --> 00:26:34,480
下面我要录下你的声音
I'm going to record your voice

327
00:26:34,810 --> 00:26:37,190
回头用这台机器重放给你听
And then play it back to you on the same machine.

328
00:26:37,850 --> 00:26:41,220
这可是来自美国的先进发明，银嗓牌留声机
This is brilliant. It's the latest thing from America :a Silvertone.

329
00:26:54,730 --> 00:26:55,750
戴上试试？
Pop these on?

330
00:26:58,210 --> 00:27:00,030
有赌注哦，回家就能发大财了！
There's a bob in this, mate. You can go home rich!

331
00:27:10,100 --> 00:27:12,130
- 你在放音乐
- 没错
- You're playing music. - I know.

332
00:27:13,050 --> 00:27:14,290
那我怎么听到我说什么？
How can I hear what I'm saying?!

333
00:27:14,940 --> 00:27:17,610
相信殿下的聪明头脑会控制自己嘴巴的
Surely a Prince's brain knows what its mouth is doing?

334
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:21,950
看起来你好像不太了解王子殿下啊
You're not well acquainted with Royal Princes, are you?

335
00:27:32,020 --> 00:27:37,010
生存还是毁灭…这是一个值得考虑的问题
to be or not to be.. that is the question

336
00:27:58,770 --> 00:28:00,950
我没救了，没救了！
Hopeless. Hopeless!

337
00:28:04,110 --> 00:28:05,240
您念得相当好啊
You were sublime.

338
00:28:06,730 --> 00:28:09,250
我会当着王子的面撒谎吗？就为了赢12便士？
Would I lie to a prince of the realm to win twelve-pence?

339
00:28:09,900 --> 00:28:14,040
我可是猜不到一个澳大利亚人要点英国小钱干嘛
I've no idea what an Australian might do for that sort of money.

340
00:28:14,570 --> 00:28:17,700
- 我放给你听
- 不用了
- let me play it back to you - No.

341
00:28:19,060 --> 00:28:20,920
那也行，我再问你些问题
Alright then, I'll get to ask you the questions.

342
00:28:21,390 --> 00:28:25,710
不麻烦了，这个疗法…不太适合我
Thank you Doctor, I don't… feel this is for me.

343
00:28:30,840 --> 00:28:34,350
占用你的时间了，再见
Thank you for your time. Bye

344
00:28:36,770 --> 00:28:37,730
公爵？
Sir?

345
00:28:43,980 --> 00:28:45,510
录音是免费的
The recording is free.

