- what's going on here? - Custos Regni, in the form of Councilors of State.

519
00:40:26,600 --> 00:40:28,920
我完全听不懂你在说什么
I cannot follow you. I'm confused and I don't understand

520
00:40:29,190 --> 00:40:31,620
- 听不明白
- 是议会的决议，陛下
- … what you're taking about  - It's the order of the Council for the State, Sir.

521
00:40:31,900 --> 00:40:35,670
- 谁帮帮我？
- 我们能代您行使权利
- would you do that? - So we may act on your behalf.

522
00:40:35,970 --> 00:40:43,310
表达的不清楚，我还是没懂什么意思
not clearly I'm afraid...I'm still confused...

523
00:40:44,020 --> 00:40:45,490
- 您同意就好
- 谢谢
But Approved. Thank you.

524
00:40:55,980 --> 00:40:59,070
- 我来帮您，陛下
- 好的
- Let me help you sir - alright

525
00:41:04,220 --> 00:41:05,470
- 谢谢陛下
- 谢谢
- thank you sir - thank you

526
00:41:11,540 --> 00:41:12,730
觉得好点了吗，陛下？
Feeling a little better Sir?

527
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:14,780
没有任何好转，我感觉很糟
No. I'm not feeling any better. I feel dreadful.

528
00:41:18,700 --> 00:41:20,270
你去滑冰玩了？
Been ice-skating?

529
00:41:22,040 --> 00:41:23,380
没有，乔治
No, George.

530
00:41:37,930 --> 00:41:39,850
他肯定没事儿
Yes, he's alright. Of course.

531
00:41:40,870 --> 00:41:43,450
我知道，亲爱的，这样长谈…
I know, darling, a talk, even a lovely long talk,

532
00:41:43,790 --> 00:41:46,960
也绝比不上和你相拥而眠
is a poor substitute for holding tight and making drowsy.

533
00:41:49,190 --> 00:41:50,190
近期见面肯定不容易
Nor making our own drowsies either,

534
00:41:50,640 --> 00:41:51,780
尤其是和你一起
as we've had to do far too often lately.

535
00:41:52,120 --> 00:41:53,740
- 大卫，吃晚饭了
- 我在和华莉丝通话
- David, the dinner - I'm on with Wallis

536
00:41:54,900 --> 00:41:55,870
是伯蒂
It's Bertie.

537
00:41:57,610 --> 00:42:02,870
不是要紧事儿。…我也不想啊
No, it's not important. No. I don't want to

538
00:42:04,410 --> 00:42:09,050
回头给我电话？好了，再见
No, telephone me later? Right, bye

539
00:42:12,200 --> 00:42:13,360
华莉丝非常想念我
Wallis misses me terribly.

540
00:42:13,840 --> 00:42:15,310
妈妈说你吃晚饭迟到了
Mama says you're late for dinner.

541
00:42:22,540 --> 00:42:25,580
她忘了老爸的表总是拨快半个小时！
She forgets Papa's bloody clocks were always half an hour fast!

542
00:42:41,700 --> 00:42:44,220
国王身体如何？希望他疼痛缓解
How is the king? I hope he is not in pain.

543
00:42:44,950 --> 00:42:46,960
没事儿了，陛下现在安静很多了
No, no, His Majesty is quieter now.

544
00:42:49,840 --> 00:42:50,740
谢谢
Thank you

545
00:42:56,180 --> 00:42:58,760
大卫，要是你父亲在
这样不守时是绝不允许的
David, if your father were here, tardiness would not be tolerated.

546
00:43:02,020 --> 00:43:04,360
不可能容忍任何这些无礼举止
None of this..unpleasantness would be tolerated

547
00:43:06,850 --> 00:43:10,880
殿下，我很欣赏您和国王有所不同的…
You know Sir, I appreciate that you are different from your father

548
00:43:11,840 --> 00:43:15,950
…性格和眼光
Both in outlook and temperament.

549
00:43:17,710 --> 00:43:20,740
我希望您明白，每当国王质询您的举止时
I want you to know that whenever the King questioned your conduct,

550
00:43:21,420 --> 00:43:27,080
我总是说好话，把您的最佳一面展现出来
I tried in your interest to present it in a most favorable light.

551
00:43:28,530 --> 00:43:31,020
我相信您会把我的利益放在心上
I can always trust you to have my best interests at heart.

552
00:43:46,750 --> 00:43:49,240
恐怕我们的守夜时间不会长了…
I'm fear our vigil will not be of long duration.

553
00:43:49,600 --> 00:43:51,580
请继续用餐，谢谢…
Please continue, thank you

554
00:44:05,130 --> 00:44:08,640
请把我们的兄弟乔治托付给仁慈的上帝
just commend our brother George to the mercy of God,

555
00:44:09,040 --> 00:44:10,810
我们的造物主，赎罪者
our Maker and Redeemer.

556
00:44:23,930 --> 00:44:25,230
国王万岁
Long live the King.

557
00:44:38,970 --> 00:44:41,230
但愿我能成为父亲那样好国王
I hope I will make good as he has made good.

558
00:45:17,760 --> 00:45:18,750
你刚才究竟是怎么了？
What on earth was that?

559
00:45:19,460 --> 00:45:22,840
可怜的华莉丝。我是解脱不了了
Poor Wallis. Now I'm trapped!

560
00:45:37,260 --> 00:45:41,320
在过去的25年的风风雨雨中
And in these last 25 crowded troubled glorious years

561
00:45:41,920 --> 00:45:44,430
国王乔治教给了我们最重要的…
If there's one thing that King George has taught

562
00:45:45,370 --> 00:45:49,400
是他的领袖风范，以及对臣民兄长般的温暖
t is the art of the leader with also a brother to his followers

563
00:45:50,430 --> 00:45:54,550
他活着的时候，是整个帝国的指路明灯
As long as he lives he was the guiding star of a great nation

564
00:45:54,990 --> 00:45:57,970
爸爸？
（广播：当国王过世，街上的小朋友们失声痛哭）
Dad? (When he died, the little children cried in the street)

565
00:45:58,140 --> 00:45:59,760
换换脑筋？
（广播：当国王过世，街上的小朋友们失声痛哭）
Time for a Shake, dad?

566
00:46:01,590 --> 00:46:02,900
- 你愿意？
- 来吧
- You sure? - Go on

567
00:46:13,020 --> 00:46:14,640
你们得绞尽脑汁了
Put your thinking caps on.

568
00:46:17,390 --> 00:46:18,510
我猜他要演苏格兰戏剧
Bet its the Scottish Play.

569
00:46:18,920 --> 00:46:20,520
我猜是《奥赛罗》，每次都是
No, I bet it's Othello. It's always Othello.

570
00:46:31,840 --> 00:46:35,410
“您害怕吗？不要怕”
（莎士比亚戏剧《暴风雨》）
“Art thou afeard? Be not afeard”

571
00:46:35,780 --> 00:46:40,040
- 你演的是 凯列班
- 老天爷，你这是碰巧猜中
- Caliban! - Oh! For heaven's sake.. that was a lucky guess!

572
00:46:40,690 --> 00:46:42,670
别理书呆子了，爸爸你继续
Don't listen to egghead. Go on, Dad.

573
00:46:43,720 --> 00:46:45,680
“这岛上充满了各种声音”
（凯列班是该剧的头号反派）
“the isle is full of noises,

574
00:46:46,240 --> 00:46:48,820
“悦耳的乐曲，使人听了愉快，不会伤人”
（《暴风雨》第三幕第三场）
Sounds and sweet airs, that give delight, and hurt not.

575
00:46:49,430 --> 00:46:52,160
“有时成千的叮咚乐器…”
Sometimes a thousand twanging instruments

576
00:46:52,580 --> 00:46:54,670
“在我耳边鸣响；有时醒来听到歌声”
Will hum about mine ears; and sometimes voices,

577
00:46:55,250 --> 00:46:59,470
“又让我沉沉睡去”
That, if then I had waked after long sleep, Will make me sleep again:”

578
00:46:59,890 --> 00:47:01,470
那好，搅局的小子，下面什么台词？
Alright, clever clogs, what comes next?

579
00:47:01,950 --> 00:47:05,310
- “然后在梦中，我在云端…”
- 是“在云端，我”
- “..and then, in dreaming, Me thought the clouds” - the clouds me thought

580
00:47:05,670 --> 00:47:06,990
“在云端…我见云层打开”
“The clouds me thought would open,

581
00:47:07,320 --> 00:47:09,630
“无数珍宝向我倾倒下来”
And show riches Ready to drop upon me; that...”

582
00:47:09,940 --> 00:47:11,830
“醒来后，哭着想要再做一遍同样的梦”
...when I waked, I cried to dream again.”

583
00:47:12,110 --> 00:47:13,310
这么想真可怜
It's such a sad thought.

584
00:47:16,370 --> 00:47:19,230
我下个病人来早了，抱歉你们得先走了
My next patient must be a bit early. You better go lads, I'm sorry.

585
00:47:21,070 --> 00:47:22,150
克利福德，你稍等一下
Won't be a moment, Clifford.

586
00:47:26,760 --> 00:47:31,930
伯蒂，他们通知我你不过来了
Bertie, they told me not to expect you.

587
00:47:35,050 --> 00:47:36,310
对你父亲的过世，我很遗憾
Sorry about your father.

588
00:47:38,390 --> 00:47:39,660
我不想冒昧打扰的…
I don't wish to intrude..

589
00:47:40,050 --> 00:47:41,710
不不，没关系，请进
No..Not at all, please come in

590
00:47:52,560 --> 00:47:55,440
我一直在练习，每天一小时
I've been practising. One hour a day.

591
00:47:56,290 --> 00:47:57,450
雷打不动
In spite of everything.

592
00:47:58,890 --> 00:48:00,190
这是怎么回事？
What's going on there?

593
00:48:01,810 --> 00:48:05,670
抱歉，我和孩子们闹着玩着
I was, sorry, mucking around with my kids.

594
00:48:09,480 --> 00:48:11,250
今天还想练习一下？
Do you feel like working today?

595
00:48:16,330 --> 00:48:17,490
柯蒂斯双翼飞机
A Curtis bi-plane.

596
00:48:17,860 --> 00:48:19,670
我准备点热牛奶
I'll put on some hot milk.

597
00:48:20,110 --> 00:48:24,420
罗格，给我来点烈酒
Logue, I'd kill for something stronger.

598
00:48:29,510 --> 00:48:31,340
我没见到我父亲的最后一面
I wasn't there for my father's death.

599
00:48:32,150 --> 00:48:33,370
我心里一直很过意不去
Still makes me sad.

600
00:48:34,320 --> 00:48:35,520
我能理解
I can imagine so.

601
00:48:37,970 --> 00:48:40,150
- 你父亲是做什么的？
- 酿酒师
- What did you father do?  - He was brewer.

602
00:48:40,700 --> 00:48:42,440
- 噢
- 至少我有免费啤酒
- Oh. - At least there was free beer.

603
00:48:44,540 --> 00:48:47,950
为纪念你父亲，干一杯
Here's to the memory of your father.

604
00:48:51,060 --> 00:48:55,300
在他…过世后，有人告诉我
I was informed, after the fact,

605
00:48:55,620 --> 00:48:59,570
我父亲的…遗言是：
my father's …last words were:

606
00:49:01,770 --> 00:49:06,260
“伯蒂比…他所有兄弟加起来…还要勇敢”
“Bertie has more.. guts than the rest of his brothers.. put together.”

607
00:49:11,070 --> 00:49:12,320
可惜他没能当面告诉我
He couldn't say that to my face.

608
00:49:18,070 --> 00:49:19,220
我哥哥
My brother.

609
00:49:21,790 --> 00:49:22,670
他怎么了
What about him?

610
00:49:25,630 --> 00:49:28,700
- 你可以唱着说
- 什么？
- Try singing it. - I'm sorry?

611
00:49:29,630 --> 00:49:30,770
你会唱什么曲子？
What songs do you know?

612
00:49:32,320 --> 00:49:34,590
- 歌谣？
- 《斯旺尼河》
- Songs? - “Swanee River”

613
00:49:35,160 --> 00:49:37,060
- 我喜欢这曲子
- 正好是我的最爱
- I love that song. - Happens to be my favorite.

614
00:49:37,880 --> 00:49:39,680
- 把和声哼给我听
- 不，肯定不唱
- Sing me the chorus. - No. Certainly not.

615
00:49:45,070 --> 00:49:46,270
我一直…想要做模型
I always.. wanted to build models.

616
00:49:48,310 --> 00:49:55,380
父亲…不会允许的。他…集邮
Father… wouldn't allow it. He.. collected stamps.

617
00:49:55,880 --> 00:49:57,060
我们也得集邮
We had to collect stamps.

618
00:49:58,200 --> 00:50:00,410
要是唱歌的话，你就可以把它做完
You can finish that off. If you sing.

619
00:50:02,290 --> 00:50:08,950
- “我哥哥大卫，啦啦啦”
- 我不会坐在这儿傻唱的
- “My brother David, doo-dah” - I'm not going to sit here wobbling

620
00:50:09,790 --> 00:50:11,170
和我别见外
You can with me.

621
00:50:12,150 --> 00:50:13,430
是啊…因为你很怪
Because… you're peculiar.

622
00:50:13,950 --> 00:50:15,290
我就把这当成赞美喽
I take that as a compliment.

623
00:50:19,210 --> 00:50:20,190
你得守规矩
Rules are rules

624
00:50:25,170 --> 00:50:29,060
我才不会…哼唱《斯旺尼河》！
I'm not…crooning “Swanee River!”

625
00:50:29,510 --> 00:50:30,590
那换成《康城赛马歌》
Try “Camptown Races” then.

626
00:50:30,880 --> 00:50:34,060
“我哥大卫，他对我说，啦啦啦啦”
“My brother D, he said to me, doodah doo-dah...”

627
00:50:34,680 --> 00:50:36,840
- 连续发声让你保持连贯
- 不行
- Continuous sound will give you flow. - No

628
00:50:48,200 --> 00:50:51,110
现在大卫成了国王，你不觉得不舒服吗？
Does it feel strange, now that David's on the throne?

629
00:50:52,580 --> 00:50:54,810
实话实说，我是松了一口气
Tell you the truth, It was a relief...

630
00:50:55,570 --> 00:51:00,070
得知…国王不是…是我
Knowing.. I wouldn't be ..King.

631
00:51:01,720 --> 00:51:05,260
不过如果他没有后代，那你就是接班人
But unless he produces an heir, you're next in line.

632
00:51:07,050 --> 00:51:10,610
然后你女儿伊丽莎白会接替你
And your daughter, Elizabeth, would then succeed you.

633
00:51:11,720 --> 00:51:15,470
“这个话题可不对头，医生，医生”
“You're barking up the wrong tree now, Doctor, Doctor.”

634
00:51:16,430 --> 00:51:19,040
叫我“莱诺”，你没结巴啊
“Lionel,” You didn't stammer.

635
00:51:20,170 --> 00:51:22,180
当然不会，我在唱歌！
Of course I didn't stammer, I was singing!

636
00:51:24,430 --> 00:51:26,290
好吧，作为小小的奖励
Well, as a little reward,

637
00:51:27,220 --> 00:51:29,130
你可以在这些支架上涂些胶水
you get to put some glue on these struts.

638
00:51:34,260 --> 00:51:37,080
- 你儿子不介意吧？
- 不会，放心吧
- your boy wouldn't mind? - No, not at all

639
00:51:41,830 --> 00:51:44,340
我和大卫很亲近
David and I were very close.

640
00:51:46,060 --> 00:51:48,300
像两头年轻的雄鹿…你懂的
Young bucks... You know.

641
00:51:49,620 --> 00:51:51,720
追求过同一个女孩？
Did you chase the same girls?

642
00:51:56,510 --> 00:52:01,100
大卫牵线搭桥很在行
David was always very helpful in arranging introductions.

643
00:52:02,990 --> 00:52:10,550
我们享受过…巴黎“波莱特”馆的顶级服务
We shared… the expert ministrations of “Paulette” in Paris.

644
00:52:17,300 --> 00:52:18,810
当然不是同时来了
Not at the same time of course.

645
00:52:23,540 --> 00:52:24,720
大卫取笑过你吗？
Did David ever tease you?

646
00:52:25,090 --> 00:52:26,520
当然，别人总是这样
Oh yes they all did.

647
00:52:27,030 --> 00:52:28,330
“伯伯伯…伯蒂”
“Buh-buh-buh-Bertie”.

648
00:52:29,930 --> 00:52:31,260
父亲也推波助澜
Father encouraged it.

649
00:52:32,640 --> 00:52:34,050
“快点说啊，小子”
“Get it out, boy!”

650
00:52:34,390 --> 00:52:35,850
以为这样就能让我不结巴
Said it would make me stop.

651
00:52:36,690 --> 00:52:39,160
他说，“我就很怕我爸”
Said...”I was afraid of my father,

652
00:52:39,860 --> 00:52:43,810
“我孩子怕我是理所当然”
and my children are damn well going to be afraid of me”.

653
00:52:46,210 --> 00:52:47,480
你是天生习惯右手吗？
Are you naturally right handed?

654
00:52:51,390 --> 00:52:57,080
我以前是左撇子…老罚我，就改成右手了
Left. I was… punished. Now I use the right.

655
00:52:58,150 --> 00:53:00,320
这在结巴患者中挺常见的
Yes, that's very common with stammerers.

656
00:53:04,210 --> 00:53:05,890
还有什么矫正之类的？
Anything other corrections?

657
00:53:06,970 --> 00:53:08,030
膝盖外翻
Knock knees.

658
00:53:11,310 --> 00:53:15,400
金属…夹板套着…昼夜都得带
Metal… splints were made...worn…day and night

659
00:53:17,640 --> 00:53:18,750
那肯定不好受
That must have been painful.

660
00:53:19,120 --> 00:53:22,170
非常难受。总算现在是直腿了
Bloody agony. Straight legs now.

661
00:53:24,980 --> 00:53:27,000
家里人谁和你最亲近
Who were you closest to in your family?

662
00:53:28,350 --> 00:53:31,310
奶妈。不过不是最早的那个
Nannies. Not my first nanny..

663
00:53:32,030 --> 00:53:34,810
她喜欢大卫，讨厌我
she loved David...hated me.

664
00:53:36,490 --> 00:53:41,070
每天我该见父母的时候…
When I.. was presented to my parents for the daily viewing,

665
00:53:41,820 --> 00:53:47,150
她…她都掐我，我就哭
she'd...She pinch me so I'd cry,

666
00:53:47,740 --> 00:53:50,040
然后我…就马上带回来让她照顾
and be…handed back to her immediately,

667
00:53:53,730 --> 00:53:55,390
然后她就不…
then she wouldn't…

668
00:53:59,350 --> 00:54:08,850
- 唱出来吧
- 她就不让我吃饭，离我远远的
- sing it - then she wouldn't feed me, far far away.”

669
00:54:12,250 --> 00:54:16,180
我父母三年以后才发现
Took my parents three years to notice.

670
00:54:17,570 --> 00:54:19,550
你也能想象的到
As you can imagine,

671
00:54:20,150 --> 00:54:23,620
给我胃留下了病根，现在还没好
it caused some stomach problems. Still.

672
00:54:29,470 --> 00:54:31,440
你兄弟乔尼呢？
What about your brother Johnnie?

673
00:54:33,530 --> 00:54:35,080
和他亲近吗？
Were you close to him?

674
00:54:35,960 --> 00:54:39,330
乔尼，人很不错
Johnnie, Sweet boy.

675
00:54:48,970 --> 00:54:55,570
有癫痫…他…有点“怪”
Epilepsy...and...he was 'different'.

676
00:54:58,660 --> 00:55:04,140
13岁死后，家里人就不再提他
He died at 13, hidden from view.

677
00:55:08,070 --> 00:55:11,910
大人说这不是光彩事儿
I've been told it's not catching.

678
00:55:15,910 --> 00:55:19,250
