the King has not always possess exclusive rights to Mrs.Simpson's favours and affections,

846
01:05:41,735 --> 01:05:44,469
现在还有个已婚的卖汽车的
sharing them with a married used car salesman,

847
01:05:44,797 --> 01:05:46,435
她是脚踩两条船
a certain Mr Guy Trundle.

848
01:05:49,266 --> 01:05:53,234
另外，传言希特勒的大使…
In addition, it is also rumored that Hitler's ambassador,

849
01:05:53,717 --> 01:05:57,350
里宾特洛甫，每天给她送17支康乃馨
Count von Ribbentrop, sends her 17 carnations every day......

850
01:05:59,869 --> 01:06:03,112
如果国王陛下继续无视内阁的忠告
Should His Majesty continue to ignore the advice of His Government,

851
01:06:03,854 --> 01:06:08,931
要么他自己退位，要么政府集体辞职
He must abdicate. Otherwise His Government has no choice but to resign.

852
01:06:09,290 --> 01:06:15,185
首相，在这个时候把国家变成一团散沙？
Prime Minister, you'd leave the country without a… government?

853
01:06:17,313 --> 01:06:18,921
究竟国王是自己随心所欲…
Does the King do what he wants,

854
01:06:20,590 --> 01:06:23,114
还是承担民众赋予的职责？
or does he do what his people expect him to do?

855
01:06:24,635 --> 01:06:26,380
唐宁街上的人们看着首相换了一届又一届
As crowds on Donning Street watch Ministers come and go

856
01:06:26,694 --> 01:06:28,095
还是绕不开一个老难题
There raised an age-old problem.

857
01:06:28,377 --> 01:06:30,973
国王能否避免私生活影响自己的职责？
Can the King separate his personal life from his public duty?

858
01:06:31,285 --> 01:06:34,614
- 怎么了，爱人？
- 有个病人很让我操心
- What's the matter, love? - I'm just having trouble with a patient

859
01:06:37,624 --> 01:06:43,778
- 这可不像你，怎么回事
- 他很害怕
- it isn't like you. Why - He's scared.

860
01:06:45,380 --> 01:06:46,568
不相信自己的力量
Frightened of his own shadow.

861
01:06:48,467 --> 01:06:49,487
所以才找你治疗啊
Isn't that why they come to you?

862
01:06:52,953 --> 01:06:57,254
这人可以真正成就一番事业
可他把功夫都花到和我作对上了
This fellow could really be somebody great. He's fighting me.

863
01:06:58,324 --> 01:06:59,507
可能他只想过平常人的生活
Perhaps he doesn't want to be great.

864
01:07:03,546 --> 01:07:04,728
是你把想法强加给他
Perhaps that's what you want.

865
01:07:09,757 --> 01:07:11,401
我说的确实有点过分了…
I might have overstepped the mark.

866
01:07:13,653 --> 01:07:16,029
那就道歉，真诚的道歉
Apologize. Deep of good.

867
01:07:28,787 --> 01:07:30,820
很抱歉，罗格先生，公爵现在很忙
I'm very sorry, Mr Logue,the Duke is busy

868
01:07:32,567 --> 01:07:35,054
我能等他，或者我回头再来
I'm happy to wait. Or I could come back later.

869
01:07:36,390 --> 01:07:38,557
我告诉过您，公爵非常忙
As I said, the Duke is terribly busy.

870
01:07:48,642 --> 01:07:49,191
麻烦了
Thank you

871
01:07:54,627 --> 01:07:55,176
多谢
Thank you

872
01:08:02,989 --> 01:08:04,837
议会不会支持这桩婚姻
Parliament will not support the marriage.

873
01:08:08,416 --> 01:08:09,736
不过反对声音也有其他的考虑
But there were other reasons for concern.

874
01:08:11,446 --> 01:08:12,798
国王这么不懂法规
He was careless with state papers.

875
01:08:13,044 --> 01:08:14,160
这么没有决断和献身精神
He lacked commitment and resolve.

876
01:08:14,846 --> 01:08:19,223
会有人担心，当和德国开战的时候
他能否顶住压力
There were those that worried where he would stand when war with Germany.

877
01:08:22,453 --> 01:08:23,248
会开战吗？
We're not coming to that?

878
01:08:24,123 --> 01:08:27,671
确实如此。虽然鲍德温首相可能不承认
Indeed we are, Sir. Prime Minister Baldwin may deny this,

879
01:08:28,204 --> 01:08:30,235
不过希特勒的野心昭然若揭
but Hitler's intent is crystal clear.

880
01:08:31,638 --> 01:08:33,006
和德国开战势在必然
War with Germany will come,

881
01:08:34,250 --> 01:08:37,699
我们需要一个强有力的国王代表我们的心声
and we will need a King we can all stand behind united.

882
01:08:38,893 --> 01:08:46,419
我担心…我哥哥现在的精神状态不怎么样
I fear..my brother is of sound mind at this time

883
01:08:48,187 --> 01:08:49,931
就没想过由你来承担吗？
Have you thought what you will call yourself?

884
01:08:54,207 --> 01:08:56,081
我…我…
I…I…

885
01:08:57,541 --> 01:09:00,853
您当然不会，德国人才这么热衷权力
Certainly not Albert, Sir. Too Germanic.

886
01:09:09,259 --> 01:09:12,076
那么想想你哥哥？在你父亲死后？
What about George? After your father?

887
01:09:14,754 --> 01:09:15,455
新国王乔治六世
George the sixth.

888
01:09:16,704 --> 01:09:19,458
他可是完美继承了父亲的品性啊，不是么
It has rather a nice continuity to it, don't you think.

889
01:09:24,256 --> 01:09:28,091
大卫！总算找到你了，你看起来精神很不好
David! Thank God. You look exhausted!

890
01:09:32,286 --> 01:09:33,114
打起精神来啊
How are you bearing up?

891
01:09:34,531 --> 01:09:37,625
伯蒂，我已经决定了，我离开
Bertie. The decision's been made. I'm… I'm going

892
01:09:40,686 --> 01:09:42,852
我不接受，你这么做太不负责任了
I cannot accept that. You are in no condition to make that decision.

893
01:09:43,210 --> 01:09:44,039
我很抱歉，没有其他的方案了
I'm afraid there's no other way.

894
01:09:46,071 --> 01:09:47,148
我一定要娶她
I must marry her.

895
01:09:50,311 --> 01:09:52,539
我决心已定。我…很抱歉
My mind's made up. I'm... sorry.

896
01:09:56,752 --> 01:09:57,731
这可不是好消息
That's a terrible thing to hear.

897
01:10:02,271 --> 01:10:04,816
对谁来说都不是。尤其对我
nobody wants that. I least of all.

898
01:10:12,262 --> 01:10:17,931
我总算能说出我自己的心声了
（我于1936年12月10日签字证明）
At long last I am able to say a few words of my own.

899
01:10:19,204 --> 01:10:21,891
我其实一直不想隐瞒什么
（爱德华签署于观景台城堡）
I have never wanted to withhold anything

900
01:10:22,798 --> 01:10:27,027
直到现在，按照法规，我才能说出想法
But until now, it has not been constitutionally possible for me to speak.

901
01:10:28,460 --> 01:10:34,731
几个小时以前，我主动解除了国王的职责
A few hours ago I discharged my last duty as King and Emperor.

902
01:10:36,960 --> 01:10:42,008
现在由我的弟弟，约克公爵继位
Now that I have been succeeded by my brother, the Duke of York

903
01:10:43,368 --> 01:10:46,666
我在这里，首先表达对他的忠诚
my first words must be to declare my allegiance to him.

904
01:10:47,876 --> 01:10:50,434
全心全意地效忠于他
This I do with all my heart.

905
01:10:54,111 --> 01:10:57,352
你们也知道我不能参加新王加冕的原因
You all know the reasons which have impelled me to renounce the throne.

906
01:10:58,948 --> 01:11:01,387
不过，请你们相信
But you must believe me when I tell you

907
01:11:02,959 --> 01:11:06,425
如果没有我心爱的女人支持
That I have found it impossible to carry the heavy burden of responsibility

908
01:11:07,530 --> 01:11:11,401
我无法承担国王的重任
and to discharge my duties as King as I would wish to do

909
01:11:12,660 --> 01:11:16,465
也更不会有勇气卸任王位
without the help and support of the woman I love...

910
01:11:18,522 --> 01:11:24,144
同样，因为我对我弟弟十分了解
And I want you to know, this decision has been made less difficult to me

911
01:11:25,475 --> 01:11:27,180
使我卸任时，能够宽慰一些
by the sure knowledge that my brother,

912
01:11:28,415 --> 01:11:31,154
他对国家公事十分熟悉
with his long training in the public affairs of this country...

913
01:11:32,951 --> 01:11:34,481
加上他的优秀品质
...and with his fine qualities...

914
01:11:35,982 --> 01:11:39,295
不会让国家接下来出现动荡
...will be able to take my place forthwith without interruption

915
01:11:40,508 --> 01:11:46,283
或者阻碍大英帝国的发展
or injury to the life and progress of the empire.

916
01:11:48,739 --> 01:11:52,292
登基会议，1936年12月12日，圣詹姆斯宫
Accession Council.St James's Palace.12th Dec,1936

917
01:13:03,315 --> 01:13:07,734
我今天与你们相见…在…
I meet you today.. in..

918
01:13:12,173 --> 01:13:14,063
…在这样的情况下…下…
in circumstances which are ..

919
01:13:32,663 --> 01:13:33,088
你们肯定会喜欢的
I'm sure you'll love it.

920
01:13:33,779 --> 01:13:36,031
谢谢，玛格丽特，装好马鞍
Thank you darling, saddles, Margret

921
01:13:36,426 --> 01:13:36,805
好的
Yes mom.

922
01:13:37,455 --> 01:13:37,808
很听话嘛
Good boy.

923
01:13:38,289 --> 01:13:41,950
- 妈妈，这是威尔逊马鞍
- 谢谢
- Mama, here's the Wilson saddle - thank you

924
01:13:43,645 --> 01:13:46,477
别担心，一会就喂你吃饭
Don't worry, we'll get you food in a minute

925
01:13:46,846 --> 01:13:49,200
妈妈，新家里会有地方放小马吗？
Mama, will we have space for our horses in our new home?

926
01:13:49,477 --> 01:13:51,202
当然，宝贝们，整个宫殿有的是房间
Of course we will, darling, we'll have a palace of rooms.

927
01:14:02,106 --> 01:14:02,574
屈膝礼
Curtsey.

928
01:14:05,549 --> 01:14:06,260
陛下
Your Majesty.

929
01:14:24,205 --> 01:14:24,585
讲话如何？
How was it?

930
01:14:37,343 --> 01:14:44,645
我试着…熟悉一下公务文件
I'm trying to… familiarise myself with what a state paper looks like.

931
01:14:49,674 --> 01:14:53,704
鲍德温的急件我一个字都看不懂
A despatch from Mr Baldwin which I don't understand a word of.

932
01:14:57,922 --> 01:14:58,596
这是哥哥的财务情况…
David's finances.

933
01:15:04,512 --> 01:15:07,537
这是圣诞讲话
The Christmas broadcast –

934
01:15:09,513 --> 01:15:10,630
我觉得还会搞砸
I think that might be a mistake.

935
01:15:11,044 --> 01:15:11,623
别担心了
Don't worry about that

936
01:15:23,655 --> 01:15:28,201
还有加冕礼。我觉得到时候会更出丑
Plans for the Coronation. I think that's an even bigger mistake.

937
01:15:32,038 --> 01:15:32,539
我不是当国王的料
I'm not a King.

938
01:15:38,769 --> 01:15:40,566
我只是个前海军军官，我就这水平
I'm a naval officer. That's all I know

939
01:15:44,135 --> 01:15:45,281
我不是当国王的料，我配不上
I'm not a King, not a king.

940
01:15:47,560 --> 01:15:52,317
- 我很抱歉，我很抱歉
- 别这样，亲爱的
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry. - No. Dear.

941
01:15:56,807 --> 01:15:58,931
我亲爱的
Dear, dear man...

942
01:16:01,793 --> 01:16:02,689
我很抱歉
I'm sorry.

943
01:16:03,613 --> 01:16:08,907
其实我两次拒绝你的求婚
You know, I refused your first two marriage proposals,

944
01:16:09,255 --> 01:16:10,909
不是因为我不爱你
Not because I didn't love you,

945
01:16:15,272 --> 01:16:14,043
而是因为我受不了王室的生活
but because I couldn't bear the idea of a royal life

946
01:16:15,434 --> 01:16:18,748
四处出访，还有公众责任
Could bear the idea of a life of tours and public duties,

947
01:16:19,740 --> 01:16:23,125
我不可能再安心过自己的小日子
a life that no longer was really to be my own.

948
01:16:25,050 --> 01:16:28,274
不过后来我想，他结巴的这么可爱
Then I thought...he stammers so beautifully...

949
01:16:28,695 --> 01:16:29,734
大家会放过他的
they'll leave us alone.

950
01:16:34,734 --> 01:16:38,528
（支持国王。上帝保佑他）
STAND BY THE KING.GOD SAVE THE KING

951
01:16:56,714 --> 01:16:58,613
等待国王的道歉
Waiting for a king to apologize,

952
01:16:58,874 --> 01:17:01,024
可要耐心等上很久
one can wait rather a long wait.

953
01:17:06,037 --> 01:17:08,033
恐怕我们迟到了一会
I'm afraid we're slightly late.

954
01:17:11,091 --> 01:17:14,193
这是我家了，我妻子去了伦敦桥
This is home. Myrtle's at bridge.

955
01:17:14,567 --> 01:17:15,688
我也让孩子们出去了
I've made sure the boys are out.

956
01:17:16,513 --> 01:17:18,971
很温馨嘛，非常温馨
It's lovely. Absolutely lovely.

957
01:17:20,961 --> 01:17:22,400
- 我能坐下吗
- 当然
- May I sit down? - Yes, of course

958
01:17:30,803 --> 01:17:31,756
需要茶水吗，夫人？
Would you like some tea, Ma'am?

959
01:17:32,202 --> 01:17:33,153
我自己来吧
Yes. I'll help myself.

960
01:17:33,963 --> 01:17:36,307
你们忙吧，难道还要我把你俩绑到一起不成？
Off you go now. Or must I knock your heads together?

961
01:17:39,047 --> 01:17:39,744
这是你赢的赌注
Here's your shilling

962
01:17:48,615 --> 01:17:55,681
我…我明白你之前的意思了，罗格
I.. understand what you were trying to say, Logue.

963
01:17:57,397 --> 01:18:00,663
是我表达方式不对，很抱歉
I went about it the wrong way. I'm sorry.

964
01:18:03,581 --> 01:18:04,780
我还是回来了
So here I am.

965
01:18:06,075 --> 01:18:10,433
希望这个国家准备好听我两分钟的静音广播了
Is the nation ready for two minutes of radio silence?

966
01:18:11,486 --> 01:18:13,745
每个病人都害怕努力半天又回到起点
Every stammer always fears they will fall back to square one.

967
01:18:15,445 --> 01:18:16,370
我绝不会让这种情况出现
I don't let that happen.

968
01:18:17,053 --> 01:18:21,399
如果我没能履行职责…大卫还能回来接任
If I fail in my duty... David could come back.

969
01:18:21,834 --> 01:18:23,007
我看了布告了
I've seen the placards

970
01:18:25,271 --> 01:18:27,856
“上帝保佑我们…国王”
“God Save Our… King!”

971
01:18:29,488 --> 01:18:30,376
他们指的不是我
They don't mean me.

972
01:18:32,453 --> 01:18:38,981
历史上君主的继任，都是在前人过世的情况下
Every other monarch in history succeeded someone who was dead,

973
01:18:40,123 --> 01:18:41,766
或者将不久于人世
Or about to be.

974
01:18:44,782 --> 01:18:49,368
我的前任现在不仅活着，还活得好好的
My predecessor is not only alive, but very much so.

975
01:18:54,494 --> 01:18:58,821
真是一团糟！我连圣诞讲话都做不了
Bloody mess! I can't even give them a Christmas Speech.

976
01:18:59,819 --> 01:19:02,005
- 像你爸爸那样？
- 是啊
- Like your Dad used to do? - Precisely.

977
01:19:03,373 --> 01:19:04,192
他已经不在了
He's not here anymore.

978
01:19:07,904 --> 01:19:09,982
他还在，就在我给你的硬币上面
Yes he is. He's on that shilling I gave you.

979
01:19:12,911 --> 01:19:13,863
放手…其实很容易
Easy enough to give away.

980
01:19:14,953 --> 01:19:16,562
你不需要心里装着父亲的影子
You don't have to carry him around in your pocket.

981
01:19:18,087 --> 01:19:18,640
或者你哥哥
Or your brother.

982
01:19:20,836 --> 01:19:24,047
五岁时能够吓到你的事情已经过去了
You don't need to be afraid of things you were afraid of when you were five.

983
01:19:31,665 --> 01:19:33,040
你现在已经完全自己做主了，伯蒂
You're very much your own man, Bertie.

984
01:19:35,711 --> 01:19:36,080
明白
Right

985
01:19:41,527 --> 01:19:42,591
以后硬币上就是你的肖像了，老兄
Your face is next, mate.

986
01:19:43,911 --> 01:19:44,405
莱诺？亲爱的？
Lionel? Dear?

987
01:19:45,576 --> 01:19:45,965
我妻子！
Myrtle!

988
01:19:47,066 --> 01:19:48,699
- 她回来了？ - 是的
- Is this your wife? - Yes.

989
01:19:50,727 --> 01:19:51,705
伯蒂，你过来
Bertie, come here

990
01:19:53,886 --> 01:19:55,709
- 罗格，你没事儿吧
- 没事儿
- Are you alright, Logue? - Yes.

991
01:19:59,149 --> 01:19:59,887
不该出去见面吗？
Shall we go through?

992
01:20:00,619 --> 01:20:01,367
相信我，这么做才行
Trust me it's important.

993
01:20:03,455 --> 01:20:03,844
怎么回事？
What is it?

994
01:20:06,271 --> 01:20:07,459
你……您……
Your... your...

995
01:20:07,781 --> 01:20:08,861
第一次叫陛下就好
It's “Your Majesty”, the first time.

996
01:20:09,712 --> 01:20:13,205
然后可以称呼“女士”，发音别发错了
After that, “Ma'am”, as in ham, not Ma'lm as in palm.

997
01:20:15,166 --> 01:20:17,977
我没和她说起过你们，先坐下歇歇
I haven't told her about us. Sit down, relax.

998
01:20:19,222 --> 01:20:23,036
我听说，你丈夫叫我丈夫“伯蒂”
I'm told your husband calls my husband Bertie

999
01:20:23,839 --> 01:20:25,401
我丈夫叫你丈夫“莱诺”
and my husband calls your husband Lionel.

1000
01:20:26,231 --> 01:20:27,849
希望你不会叫我“莉丝”
（王后名字的昵称）
I trust you won't call me Liz.

1001
01:20:28,991 --> 01:20:32,207
陛下，您可以称呼我为罗格夫人
Your Majesty, you may call me Mrs Logue, Ma'am.

1002
01:20:33,061 --> 01:20:34,376
见到你很高兴，罗格夫人
Very nice to meet you, Mrs Logue

1003
01:20:37,197 --> 01:20:39,069
- 罗格，咱们不能整天猫在这里
- 必须这样
- Logue, we can't stay here all day. - Yes we can.

1004
01:20:39,386 --> 01:20:41,142
- 罗格…
- 我得等个恰当时机才行
- Logue.. - Look, I need to wait for the opportune moment.

1005
01:20:41,777 --> 01:20:44,122
- 你这是怕老婆
- 说的很对！
- You're being a coward! - You're damn right.

1006
01:20:46,339 --> 01:20:47,190
快出去，一家之主
Get out there, man!

1007
01:20:49,990 --> 01:20:53,400
你好啊，亲爱的老婆，你回来早了
Oh! Hello, Myrtle darling! You're early.

1008
01:20:54,244 --> 01:20:55,919
我相信你们已经见过面了
I believe you two have met!

1009
01:20:56,610 --> 01:21:00,792
不过还没见过…国王乔治六世吧？
I don't believe you know....King George VI?

1010
01:21:01,535 --> 01:21:02,334
见到您很高兴
It's very nice to meet you.

1011
01:21:07,203 --> 01:21:09,385
陛下能一起吃晚饭吗？
Will their Majesties be staying to dinner?

1012
01:21:11,463 --> 01:21:14,509
我们很想，这么盛情邀请，不过…
We would love to, such a treat, but alas...

1013
01:21:15,553 --> 01:21:17,360
我们之前有其他安排了，真是可惜
a previous engagement. What a pity.

1014
01:21:33,606 --> 01:21:34,226
大主教
Archbishop.

1015
01:21:34,917 --> 01:21:36,244
欢迎您，陛下
Welcome your Majesty.

1016
01:21:37,821 --> 01:21:40,007
这里改造的十分壮观
What a glorious transformation, Sir.

1017
01:21:41,096 --> 01:21:43,525
希望我们继续工作不会妨碍您
I hope you'll forgive us if we continue our preparations.

1018
01:21:45,448 --> 01:21:50,405
请允许我讲一下仪式过程
Now, allow me to guide you through the ceremony.

1019
01:21:55,494 --> 01:21:59,518
我们从西入口开始，然后到中间广场
We begin, of course at the West Door, then into the nave.

1020
01:22:02,007 --> 01:22:04,766
大主教，听说你的所有宣言都会被广播
I see all your pronouncements are to be broadcast, Archbishop.

1021
01:22:06,215 --> 01:22:10,824
是啊，无线电是把双刃剑
Ah, yes, wireless is indeed a Pandora's Box.

1022
01:22:11,913 --> 01:22:15,057
恐怕我也得批准新闻摄影机的拍摄
I'm afraid I've also had to permit the newsreel cameras.

1023
01:22:15,652 --> 01:22:18,688
回头我会亲自剪辑的
The product of which I shall personally edit.

1024
01:22:19,553 --> 01:22:21,068
肯定毫不犹豫
Without momentary hesitation.

1025
01:22:22,241 --> 01:22:25,174
这位是哈雷街的罗格医生
This is Dr. Logue from Harley Street.

1026
01:22:25,645 --> 01:22:28,635
他是我的语言矫正医生
He's… my speech therapist.

1027
01:22:30,239 --> 01:22:30,657
大人
Your Grace

1028
01:22:31,205 --> 01:22:33,980
要是我知道陛下需要协助
Had I known Your Majesty was seeking assistance

1029
01:22:34,237 --> 01:22:35,669
我肯定会亲自推荐人选
I would've made my own recommendation.

1030
01:22:37,221 --> 01:22:41,113
罗格医生需要参加加冕礼
Dr. Logue will be attending the Coronation.

1031
01:22:42,536 --> 01:22:44,307
我当然可以和主持牧师说一下
Well of course I shall speak to the Dean,

1032
01:22:44,625 --> 01:22:46,191
不过可能会很难办
but it will be extremely difficult.

1033
01:22:46,959 --> 01:22:54,077
我希望…医生坐在…国王的包厢中
I should like… the Doctor to be seated in the… King's Box.

1034
01:22:56,216 --> 01:22:58,367
可您的家人才能坐在那里，陛下
But members of your Family will be seated there, Sir.

1035
01:22:58,987 --> 01:22:59,980
所以他正合适
That why it's suitable.

1036
01:23:03,154 --> 01:23:05,071
现在，如果大人不介意的话
我们需要场地做一下排练
And now, if you don't mind, your grace we need the premises.

1037
01:23:05,357 --> 01:23:07,502
这位先生，这里可是威斯敏斯特教堂！
My dear fellow, this is Westminster Abbey!

1038
01:23:07,886 --> 01:23:09,596
教会一定要为陛下做好准备
The Church must prepare his Majesty.

1039
01:23:10,027 --> 01:23:12,029
我的准备同样重要
My preparations are equally important.

1040
01:23:17,255 --> 01:23:19,176
需要无人打扰，希望您不要介意
With complete privacy. If you don't mind.

1041
01:23:21,766 --> 01:23:23,574
这也是我的意思，大人
Those are my wishes, Your Grace.

1042
01:23:25,171 --> 01:23:29,672
那今晚我把教堂给您处置
I will place the Abbey at Your Majesty's disposal...this evening.

1043
01:23:31,388 --> 01:23:31,879
陛下
Your Majesty.

1044
01:23:53,171 --> 01:23:55,849
看，他又来了。咱们走
Look, he again. Come on.

1045
01:24:03,902 --> 01:24:06,709
真不敢相信我走在乔叟、亨德尔、狄更斯的墓上
（这些诗人葬在教堂的诗人角落里）
I can't believe I'm walking on Chaucer and Handel and Dickens.

1046
01:24:10,789 --> 01:24:12,089
准备好了？开始吧
Everything alright? Let's get cracking.

1047
01:24:14,700 --> 01:24:17,834
我来这儿不是彩排的，罗格“医生”
I'm not here to rehearse, "Doctor" Logue.

1048
01:24:21,356 --> 01:24:22,144
叫我莱诺
Call me Lionel

1049
01:24:24,362 --> 01:24:27,351
是啊，你是一直…
True, you never…

1050
01:24:29,430 --> 01:24:34,438
不叫自己医生，是我自己这么称呼的
called yourself 'Doctor'.I did that for you.

1051
01:24:38,575 --> 01:24:46,911
没有训练，没有文凭，没有…执照
no training, no diploma, no.. qualifications.

1052
01:24:47,899 --> 01:24:51,196
穷有一身的胆量
Just a great deal of nerve.

1053
01:24:52,757 --> 01:24:54,590
你这是来秘密审问我喽？
the star chamber inquisition, is it?

1054
01:24:55,246 --> 01:25:00,473
你还希望能信任你，公平对待你
You asked for trust and.. total equality.

1055
01:25:01,692 --> 01:25:03,028
伯蒂，我听了你在温布利的讲话
Bertie, I heard you at Wembley,

1056
01:25:03,929 --> 01:25:04,396
我在场
I was there.

1057
01:25:06,197 --> 01:25:09,761
我儿子劳里说“你不能想法帮帮这个可怜人”？
My son Laurie said “Do you think you could help that poor man?”

1058
01:25:10,129 --> 01:25:10,928
就凭一个失业演员？
What, as a failed actor!?

1059
01:25:11,542 --> 01:25:16,932
我确实不是医生，我也曾经参加表演
It's true, I'm not a doctor, and yes I acted a bit,

1060
01:25:18,621 --> 01:25:21,708
我以前在酒吧朗诵，在学校教书
I recited in pubs and taught elocution in schools.

1061
01:25:22,830 --> 01:25:27,187
战争来临时，大量前线士兵因为惊吓…
When the Great War came, our soldiers were pouring back from the front,

1062
01:25:27,460 --> 01:25:29,000
…回到后方了，就不再开口说话
shell-shocked and unable to speak

1063
01:25:30,797 --> 01:25:33,367
有人说，“莱诺，你不是对语言挺在行么”
and somebody said,"Lionel, you're very good at all this speech stuff.

1064
01:25:33,664 --> 01:25:34,759
“你能想法帮帮他们吗”
Do you think you could possibly help these poor buggers”.

1065
01:25:37,268 --> 01:25:39,715
我尝试了肌肉治疗、练习、放松
I did muscle therapy, exercise, relaxation,

1066
01:25:40,166 --> 01:25:41,205
不过我知道想根治还得更深入
but I knew I had to go deeper.

1067
01:25:43,920 --> 01:25:45,701
这些小伙子们因为恐惧哭出声来
Those poor young blokes had cried out in fear,

1068
01:25:46,111 --> 01:25:47,048
却没有人去用心听他们说话
and no-one was listening to them.

1069
01:25:50,028 --> 01:25:51,829
我的工作，是给他们说话的自信
My job was to give them faith in their voice

1070
01:25:53,898 --> 01:25:55,798
让他们知道，总有位朋友愿意倾听
and let them know that a friend was listening.

1071
01:25:58,461 --> 01:26:00,160
这不是和你的治疗很像吗，伯蒂
That must ring a few bells with you, Bertie.

1072
01:26:06,007 --> 01:26:07,256
你这样太拔高自己了
You give a very noble account of yourself.

1073
01:26:08,265 --> 01:26:09,739
你去问问，都是事实
Make inquiries. It's all true.

1074
01:26:10,543 --> 01:26:11,649
我都问过了！
Inquiries have been made!

1075
01:26:11,962 --> 01:26:15,004
你是不知道有多少人巴不得帮我打听清楚
You have no idea who I have breathing down my neck.

1076
01:26:16,777 --> 01:26:22,672
我为你做了担保，你却连证书…都没有
I vouched for you and you have no…credentials.

1077
01:26:23,098 --> 01:26:26,175
可我治疗成功了很多人！我没有证书给你看
But lots of success! I can't show you a certificate

1078
01:26:27,122 --> 01:26:28,363
那时也没有系统的训练机构
there was no training then.

1079
01:26:28,628 --> 01:26:29,914
我只是按着经验行事
All I know I know by experience,

1080
01:26:30,262 --> 01:26:32,865
是这场战争，给了我经验
and that war was some experience.

1081
01:26:36,465 --> 01:26:38,242
我的牌子上写的是“L 罗格 语言矫正”
May plaque says, ‘L.Logue, Speech Defects'.

1082
01:26:38,687 --> 01:26:40,256
我没有自称医生
No Dr., no letters after my name.

1083
01:26:46,757 --> 01:26:47,474
关我进监狱好了
Lock me in the Tower.

1084
01:26:48,095 --> 01:26:48,957
如果我有机会的话！
I would if I could!

1085
01:26:49,258 --> 01:26:49,944
什么罪名？
On what charge?

1086
01:26:50,251 --> 01:26:52,029
诈骗！战争迫在眉睫
Fraud! With war looming,

1087
01:26:52,367 --> 01:26:55,613
你让这国家的国王不能说话
you've saddle this nation with a voiceless King.

1088
01:26:57,000 --> 01:26:58,731
毁了我家庭的幸福
You destroyed the happiness of my family...

1089
01:26:59,048 --> 01:27:02,761
这都是精心诱捕一个知名病人的圈套
all for the sake of ensnaring a star patient

1090
01:27:03,099 --> 01:27:05,814
你不可能治好！
you couldn't possibly hope to assist!

1091
01:27:08,410 --> 01:27:12,630
我会像疯国王乔治三世那样…
It'll be like mad …King George the Third,

1092
01:27:14,925 --> 01:27:20,265
留下个结巴国王乔治的名号
there'll be…Mad King George the Stammerer,

1093
01:27:23,546 --> 01:27:26,292
在这样的关键时刻辜负人民的期望
who let his people down so badly in their hour of need!

1094
01:27:28,111 --> 01:27:30,570
你这成何体统？起来！
这不是你坐的！起来
What're you doing? Get up! You can't sit there! Get up

1095
01:27:30,891 --> 01:27:31,802
有什么？不过是把椅子
Why not? It's a chair.

1096
01:27:32,100 --> 01:27:37,137
这不是…这是…圣爱德华的椅子
No, it's not, that is… Saint Edward's Chair-

1097
01:27:37,480 --> 01:27:38,863
人们还往上刻名字呢！
People have carved their name into it!

1098
01:27:39,170 --> 01:27:41,776
这椅子上坐过所有的国王和王后
That chair is the seat on which every King and Queen

1099
01:27:42,224 --> 01:27:43,405
不过是块石头上的椅子
It's held in place by a large rock!

1100
01:27:43,696 --> 01:27:45,089
这是命运之石
That is the Stone of Scone,

1101
01:27:45,504 --> 01:27:48,028
- 你怎么藐视一切
- 我不在乎
- you are trivialising everything - I don't care.

1102
01:27:48,335 --> 01:27:51,126
我不在乎有多少王室成员的屁股坐过这里
I don't care how many Royal arses have sat in this chair-

1103
01:27:51,407 --> 01:27:52,078
你听我说！你听我说！
Listen to me... ! Listen to me... ! Listen to me... !

1104
01:27:52,354 --> 01:27:52,934
- 听你的？为什么
- Listen to you?! By what right?

1105
01:27:53,180 --> 01:27:54,207
我有权，你必须服从，我是国王！
My divine right, if you must! I'm your King!!!

1106
01:27:54,504 --> 01:27:55,965
你才不是，亲自跟我说…
Noooo you're not! Told me so yourself.

1107
01:27:56,262 --> 01:27:59,067
…你不想当。我干嘛要听你的？
Said you didn't want it. Why should I waste my time listening to you?

1108
01:27:59,318 --> 01:28:00,390
因为我有发表意见的权利！
Because I have a right to be heard!

1109
01:28:00,665 --> 01:28:01,216
我的声音有份量！
I HAVE A VOICE!!!

1110
01:28:07,572 --> 01:28:08,386
是的，你有
Yes you do.

1111
01:28:18,984 --> 01:28:20,419
伯蒂，你有毅力
You have such perseverance, Bertie,

1112
01:28:20,690 --> 01:28:21,477
你是我认识的最勇敢的人
you're the bravest man I know.

1113
01:28:23,272 --> 01:28:24,171
你会成为一个相当好的国王
you'll make a bloody good king.

1114
01:28:33,110 --> 01:28:34,497
这究竟是怎么回事，陛下？
What on earth's going on, Sir?

1115
01:28:34,914 --> 01:28:35,968
大主教，没事的
It's quite all right, Archbishop.

1116
01:28:37,016 --> 01:28:40,683
罗格先生，我已经找到了一个治疗师替换你
Mr Logue, you should know that I have found a replacement English specialist

1117
01:28:40,996 --> 01:28:45,255
简历无可挑剔。这里也不再需要你的服务了
with impeccable credentials. Hence, your services will no longer be required.

1118
01:28:45,956 --> 01:28:46,474
怎么回事？
I'm sorry?

1119
01:28:46,806 --> 01:28:49,340
国王可以询问或者被告知结果
Your Majesty's function is to consult and be advised.

1120
01:28:49,745 --> 01:28:52,587
您没询问过我，那我告诉您结果
You didn't consult, but you've just been advised.

1121
01:28:55,101 --> 01:29:01,849
那我告诉你：这件事上，我必须自己做主
Now I advise you: in this personal matter I will make my own decision.

1122
01:29:02,596 --> 01:29:06,579
我关心的是，王冠加冕在明君的头上
My concern is for the head upon which I must place the crown.

1123
01:29:07,332 --> 01:29:08,567
我欣赏您的坦诚，大主教
I appreciate that Archbishop

1124
01:29:11,291 --> 01:29:11,938
可这是我的头
but it's my head!

1125
01:29:14,536 --> 01:29:15,314
那卑职告退
Your humble servant.

1126
01:29:23,526 --> 01:29:24,105
谢谢，伯蒂
Thank you Bertie.

1127
01:29:27,550 --> 01:29:28,212
我们排练一下？
Shall we rehearse?

1128
01:29:29,097 --> 01:29:30,117
来吧，坐在你位置上
Come on, up on your perch

1129
01:29:38,502 --> 01:29:41,027
当你和王后进入西门
Now when you and Elizabeth enter through West door,

1130
01:29:41,697 --> 01:29:45,004
人们会唱赞歌迎接你们：“对我说，我就欢喜”
you'll be greeted with the hymn “I Was Glad When They Said Unto Me.”

1131
01:29:45,864 --> 01:29:47,427
不过你们欢喜不了
You won't actually be that glad,

1132
01:29:47,744 --> 01:29:48,659
他们会唱上很久很久
because they sing it for a great long time.

1133
01:29:51,087 --> 01:29:54,886
然后你的朋友，主教大人会登上楼梯
Then your friend the Archbishop will ponce up the stairs towards you

1134
01:29:56,033 --> 01:30:00,499
对你说“陛下，您愿意宣誓吗？”
and say, "Sir, is Your Majesty willing to take The Oath?"

1135
01:30:02,398 --> 01:30:02,987
“我愿意”
“I am willing”.

1136
01:30:03,523 --> 01:30:07,298
你当然愿意!我在后排听听效果如何
Course you are! I'll see what it sounds like from the cheap seats

1137
01:30:07,574 --> 01:30:08,705
得让你的老奶妈也听得到
so even your old nanny can hear.

1138
01:30:10,108 --> 01:30:13,763
“您愿意统治大不列颠的领土…”
“Will you govern your peoples of Great Britain, Ireland,

1139
01:30:14,086 --> 01:30:20,154
还包含爱尔兰，加拿大，澳大利亚，新西兰，
并尊重他们的土地和习俗吗？”
Canada, Australia and New Zealand according to their lands and customs?”

1140
01:30:21,817 --> 01:30:23,072
“我庄严起誓，我愿意”
"I solemnly promise so do so."

1141
01:30:23,630 --> 01:30:24,992
大声点！后面听不到
LOUDER! I can't hear you up the back.

1142
01:30:25,298 --> 01:30:27,177
“我庄严起誓，我愿意！”
“I SOLEMNLY PROMISE TO DO SO!”

1143
01:30:27,953 --> 01:30:32,673
非常好！“您愿意在所有决定中…”
Very good! "Will you to your power cause Law and Justice,

1144
01:30:32,980 --> 01:30:35,550
“都考虑到法律、公平和仁慈吗？”
in Mercy, to be executed in all your judgments?"

1145
01:30:36,522 --> 01:30:37,469
“我愿意”，“我愿意！”
"I will." “I WILL!”

1146
01:30:38,349 --> 01:30:41,769
然后会有人们共同努力之类的话…等等
Then a long bit about upholding the faith goes on, rubbish, rubbish

1147
01:30:42,433 --> 01:30:43,306
最后，你需要说…
To which you finally say...

1148
01:30:44,657 --> 01:30:48,757
“刚才我所承诺过的”
“These things which I have here before promised,

1149
01:30:50,821 --> 01:30:53,612
“我会为之鞠躬尽瘁，请上帝保佑我”
I will perform and keep. So help me God.”

1150
01:30:54,672 --> 01:30:56,683
需要说的就这么多，简短四句话
That's all you have to say. Four short responses,

1151
01:30:57,589 --> 01:30:58,741
亲吻法典，签上誓言
kiss the book and sign the oath.

1152
01:30:59,688 --> 01:31:00,661
大功告成：你就是国王了
There you are: you're King.

1153
01:31:02,059 --> 01:31:02,438
很简单
Easy.

1154
01:31:16,619 --> 01:31:18,551
你差点把王冠戴反了，大主教
You nearly crowned him backwards Archbishop!

1155
01:31:20,455 --> 01:31:23,982
有人把王冠正面的线拆掉了，陛下
Someone had removed the thread marking the front of the Crown, Sir.

1156
01:31:24,965 --> 01:31:26,456
可别这样了，大主教
Try not lose the thread, Archbishop.

1157
01:31:28,104 --> 01:31:29,691
大主教，你戴偏了王冠
Archbishop, your missing Papa.

1158
01:31:35,102 --> 01:31:37,720
非常好，非常好，大主教
Very good, very good. Archbishop.

1159
01:31:39,706 --> 01:31:42,317
我希望陛下对于结果很满意
Well, I hope Your Majesties are thrilled with the result.

1160
01:31:42,880 --> 01:31:45,793
你可以把机器关掉了
You can switch that machine off now.

1161
01:31:46,196 --> 01:31:47,233
不，等等，继续放吧
No, wait, keeping going.

1162
01:31:48,998 --> 01:31:49,957
主教请坐
Do have a seat, Archbishop.

1163
01:31:57,380 --> 01:32:02,347
（希特勒）
(Hitler)

1164
01:32:10,180 --> 01:32:12,602
爸爸，他在说什么？
Papa, what's he saying?

1165
01:32:13,569 --> 01:32:16,442
听不懂，不过听起来他说得很流利
I don't know, but he seems to be saying it rather well.

1166
01:32:37,270 --> 01:32:45,248
陛下，我今天请求见您是要辞掉首相职务
Sir, I have asked to see you today in order to tender my resignation as Prime Minister.

1167
01:32:47,569 --> 01:32:49,857
鲍德温先生，我很遗憾
I am so sorry to hear that, Mr Baldwin.

1168
01:32:51,044 --> 01:32:53,764
